modules.description: This module implements interval creation and manipulation using floating-point bounds and associated values. It provides functions to construct intervals from bounds and values, convert tuples to intervals, and extract tuple representations from intervals. Use cases include representing time ranges, numeric ranges with metadata, or spatial intervals in geometric algorithms.

This module implements an interval tree data structure for efficiently querying intervals that contain specific floating-point values. It supports construction from lists of intervals or triplets of bounds and values, and provides operations to extract intervals containing a query point. Use cases include scheduling systems to find overlapping time slots, geometric algorithms to detect spatial overlaps, and range-based data analysis in numeric datasets.
